content:
Prerequisites You should have all the modules installed before compiling You should have all the requirements for the python file before compiling it Install Nuitka on Windows Go to Go to nuitka.net/download/windows which will download a .msi file
Run the file and click on &ldquo;More info&rdquo;
Click on &ldquo;Run anyway&rdquo;
Click on &ldquo;Install for all users&rdquo; then click &ldquo;Next&rdquo;
Specify the python 3.9 compiler, its easier to use the Python 3.9 from registry and click on &ldquo;Finish&rdquo;
Confirm installation 1 nuitka --version Compile 1 py -m nuitka --minhw64 &lt;filename.py&gt; --standalone --onefile This will make 2 folders with logs and other Nuitka files and a .exe file from your .py file.
I recommend using:
1 py -m nuitka --minhw64 &lt;filename.py&gt; --standalone --onefile --remove-output where --remove-output removes the 2 folders after compiling the .exe file.
